Minister Zweli Mkhize confirms total of 596 060 cases of Coronavirus COVID-19  19 August 2020 As of today, a cumulative total of 596 060 confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa have been recorded with 3 916 new cases identified. Case Data Province Total cases for 19 August 2020 Percentage total Eastern Cape 84362 14,2 Free State 33163 5,6 Gauteng 202011 33,9 KwaZulu-Natal 107271 18,0 Limpopo 11944 2,0 Mpumalanga 22067 3,7 North West 23641 4,0 Northern Cape 8341 1,4 Western Cape 103210 17,3 Unknown 50 0,0 Total 596060 100,0 Testing Data The total number of tests conducted to date is 3 455 671 with 25 324 new tests conducted since the last report. Sector Total tested  New tested  PRIVATE 1 950 552 56% 15 906 63% PUBLIC 1 505 119 44% 9 418 37% Total 3 505 119  25 324  Reported Deaths and Recoveries Regrettably we report a further 159 COVID-19 related deaths- 37 from Eastern Cape, 43 from Gauteng, 45 from KwaZulu-Natal, 5 from Free State and 29 from Western Cape. This brings the total COVID-19 related cumulative deaths to 12 423 We convey our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the health care workers who treated the deceased. The recoveries now stand at 491 441 which translates to a recovery rate of 82% Province Deaths Recoveries Eastern Cape 2670 79947 Free State 542 19548 Gauteng 3061 167812 KwaZulu-Natal 1788 82599 Limpopo 159 10281 Mpumalanga 214 19436 North West 214 14980 Northern Cape 100 4961 Western Cape 3675 91877 Total 12423 491441 Issued by Department of Health, 19 August 2020